<TITLE> AL invites BNP to council </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 23 (bdnews24.com)The ruling Awami League on Thursday invited main opposition party, the BNP, to its council slated for Friday. An AL delegation handed the invitation letter addressed to secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain at BNP's Naya Paltan headquarters at midday. Office secretary Rizvi Ahmed received the letter. Deputy secretary Mrinal Kanti Sen, Akhter Hossain and Khalid Mahmud Chowdhury MP were in the AL delegation. Mrinal told bdnews24.com, "Invitation to party chairperson Khaleda Zia will be sent to her office in the evening." Acting general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam on Wednesday told reporters that political parties other than those who were involved in anti-liberation war activities would be invited. The council will be held at the Bangabandhu International Conference Centre. d
